overall_assessment.Performance Examples_FOR_EXAMPLE:
I'd like to bring awareness to some of my most proud accomplishments at Ennead Architects:

1. Provisioned the following security solutions:
Defender for Endpoint (many integrations across azure and devices)
Defender for Cloud Apps (integrated)
SIEM - Sentinel (single pane of glass view of all processes with automations)
Defender for Identity (critical risk protection integrated with Conditional access)
Defender for Office 365 
Mobile app protection (personal device access to Ennead resources)
Purview (DLP, AIP) (ongoing))
Threat Intelligence integrations (SIEM, MDE, MDCA, SIEM)
Conditional access (MFA, Risk blocking and Data loss prevention integrations and more)
Ransomware protections with OneDrive for Business rollout (company-wide)
Custom alerting and automations around risky users
Web content and AI rule mitigations
Daily, weekly and monthly security reviews and responses to many events including malware, content blocking and MITRE attack mitigations
Enterprise app and app registration reviews and support

2. Infrastructure:
Migrated Newforma from on-premises into Azure hosted IAAS platform
Deployed fusion connect IP Telephony integrations with Teams (handled all Azure and M365 integrations in collaboration with a team member)
OneDrive for Business implementation company wide
Repaired hundreds of broken tokens across all company workstations (mandatory to manage devices and to secure devices into the cloud)
Rolled out MECM and integrated MECM with Intune (remote control, device repair and detailed asset reporting funneled into Intune)
Windows 11 upgrades (ongoing)
Argos migrations (ongoing)
Printer server migration to the cloud (ongoing)
Desktop support
Application packaging including custom built application such as Drive Mapper and others

3. Other
Daily 3rd level support for business teams fielding many requests to resolve issues, provide access to users, repair items
Daily administration of Email, calendars, guest users (partner access)
Resolved many issues with internal systems emailing and alerting such as Newforma and NetApp monitoring
Support ticket troubleshooting and resolution
Custom solutions such as EPM (users can elevate specific apps to administrator for specific use cases ) (ongoing))
Shanghai migration project (Ongoing)
Custom requests such as eDiscovery or assisting partners to access systems

overall_assessment.Additional Resources_FOR_EXAMPLE: We have three offices now. By implementing structured channels for knowledge exchange and strategic alignment, we can better leverage our collective intelligence. This will allow each market to actively learn from the others' experiences, provide cross-regional support, and efficiently share resources, ultimately strengthening our firm's global position and driving unified growth.
overall_assessment.Performance Examples_FOR_EXAMPLE: Continued building up the connections with the clients, this year, I've brought three ByteDance competitions, one JD competition (a new client), one lab project in Shenzhen and one cultural project in Shaoxing.

performance_comments.Communication Comments_FOR_EXAMPLE: I strive to ensure my communication is clear and effective, whether in verbal discussions or written correspondence. I make a conscious effort to listen actively to clients, our design teams, and local partners, aiming to fully understand their perspectives and ensure we are aligned. I try to tailor my communication style to the audience, whether explaining a complex design intent to a client or coordinating technical details with our consultants. There is always room to improve, and I welcome feedback to ensure my communication remains as effective as possible.
performance_comments.Collaboration Comments_FOR_EXAMPLE: I believe the best architectural solutions emerge from truly collaborative efforts. My approach is to facilitate and support the team, ensuring everyone—from our visionary designers to our technical staff and external partners—has a voice and feels empowered to contribute. In the China market, I see my role as a bridge, helping to synthesize diverse ideas and cultural nuances into a cohesive project direction. I am grateful for the talented teams I work with and focus on creating an environment of mutual trust and shared purpose.
performance_comments.Professionalism Comments_FOR_EXAMPLE: I endeavor to uphold the highest standards of professionalism that reflect well on Ennead's reputation. This means taking full accountability for my responsibilities, meeting commitments reliably, and always acting with integrity. I try to maintain a calm and constructive demeanor, especially during challenging phases of a project, focusing on solutions rather than problems. I view professionalism as an ongoing practice and consistently look for ways to better represent our firm's values to our clients and partners.
performance_comments.Technical Knowledge & Expertise Comments: My technical knowledge is built on a strong foundation in architectural design principles, project delivery methodologies, and business development strategies specific to the built environment. I strive to continuously learn from our technical teams and consultants to ensure our proposals and project plans are not only creative but also technically sound and feasible for the China market. This is particularly important when new market opportunities emerge, such as a shift towards sustainable design or a new building typology we will do in China, i.e. Healthcare and Institutional Laboratory.
performance_comments.Workflow Implementation, Management, Exe: I focus on creating and managing efficient workflows to see projects and strategic initiatives through from conception to completion. This involves coordinating closely with our design, marketing, and finance teams to develop winning proposals, and then managing the project lifecycle to deliver on those promises. I rely on our established firm-wide systems and actively seek to improve local implementation, ensuring our operations in China are seamless, integrated, and effective in supporting our creative and business goals.
